<tr>
<td class="article-body"><P>
<TABLE cellSpacing=2 cellPadding=0 bgColor=#ffffd7 border=2>
<TBODY>
<TR>
<TD>
<P><FONT color=#4a4a4a><STRONG>Tuesday 14 August 2007</STRONG></FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#4a4a4a><STRONG>Marat was upset about his loss in the 1st Round at Cincinnati Masters to Nicolas Kiefer and the game that he played but realises he&nbsp;has to move on.</STRONG></FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#4a4a4a><STRONG>The one good thing is that Marat is delighted with the way he and his new coach Hernan Gumy are working together and as such they have extended their initial contract which ran until after the US Open to the end of the year. At the end of the year they will re - evaluate the situation and all being well continue together next year.</STRONG></FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#4a4a4a><STRONG>Marat knows he has to get his game back together again, to be more agressive and to be the old Marat where he controlled the game not the other way round. Hernan has identified these points to Marat and they are working on them together.</STRONG></FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#4a4a4a><STRONG>Marat flew to Miami immediately after the match and will be there for 8 days practising.He and Hernan have identified areas they wish to work on. Marat knows that the it will not be a miracle cure but he is determined to keep working and finding a way to get back in the top where he belongs.<BR><BR>He will arrive in New York for the US Open on Wednesday 22nd August.</STRONG></FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#4a4a4a><STRONG>Marat said: I just want to thank all my fans once again for their patience and support - they are always there for me whatever happens and I hope that sometime real soon I will be able to give them moments of joy again.</STRONG></FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#4a4a4a><STRONG>After the US Open Marat will be involved in Davis Cup semi finals between Russia and the Germany in Moscow&nbsp;and then goes to Asia to the Kingfisher Open in Mumbai in India - his first time at this tournament.</STRONG></FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#4a4a4a><STRONG>Marat remembers that back in 2004 having lost in the 1st Round at the US Open to Thomas Enqvist, he went to the Beijing Open for the 1st time in Asia and won it beating Mikhail Youzhny in the finals 7.6(4) 7.5. This win turned his year around as he went on to win both Madrid and Paris Bercy Indoor Masters - back to back. And he reached the semi finals of the Houston Masters Cup - so the year had a successful end and he is hoping that playing in Asia again will also bring that same good fortune.</STRONG></FONT></P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></P></td>
</tr>

